; short-list of SB&#39;s list. SB list gives the avataras of Supreme Bein=\r\ng (&quot;Purusha&quot; as it calls). Dasavataras OTOH are specifically of Vishnu, who=\r\n is the &quot;sustaining principle&quot; of Purusha. Dattatreya is an avatara of Brah=\r\nma, Vishnu and Shiva together, i.e. creative, sustaining and destructive pr=\r\ninciples of Purusha combined together. That is why he is not among Dasavata=\r\nras. That does not make him any less or more. His purpose/functionality is =\r\nsimply different from that of Rama, Krishna, Narasimha, or Venkateswara. Ju=\r\nst in terms of &quot;popularity&quot;, he is actually more popular than some of the d=\r\nasavataras.\n=A0\nSecondly, rather than *comparing* avataras in terms like &quot;l=\r\ness&quot; or more in &quot;spirituality&quot;, try to *understand* avataras from the point=\r\n of view of what functionality and role they play in the functioning of col=\r\nlective cosmic consciousness. THAT is the key to understanding them and the=\r\nir place in cosmos. And also to internalizing them eventually..\n=A0\n*=A0=A0=\r\n=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n=A0\nWhether you call the Supreme B=\r\neing as Purusha or Krishna or Shiva or Surya or Narayana does not really ma=\r\ntter, for Scriptures are clear that He is beyond names or descriptions.\n=A0=\r\n\nIf your devotion to Him is steadfast, if your notion of Him expands with t=\r\nime beyond the initial notions you start off with, and if the paramatmamsa =\r\nin you is able to resonate to Him and the conditioning of your jeevatmamsa =\r\nis being overcome, that is all that matters!\n=A0\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n--=\r\n------\nAstrology & Spirituality Resources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n-=\r\n-------\n\n=A0\n\n\n&gt;________________________________\n&gt; From: rajarshi nandy &lt;ra=\r\njarshi14@...&gt;\n&gt;To: &quot;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;vedic-wisdom@yah=\r\noogroups.com&gt; \n&gt;Sent: Monday, May 6, 2013 8:07 AM\n&gt;Subject: 