.\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;We=A0human beings are creatures of imagination. Whenever an =\r\nAvatar appears on the earth,=A0most of the great Mahatmas who appear after =\r\nthe Avatara, remain=A0overawed by the=A0character of the last Avatara=A0bec=\r\nause invariable in the context of the desh-kaal-patra of those times, the l=\r\nife of the Avatara shows actions performed which are=A0way beyond=A0imagina=\r\ntion for *those times*. Such a situation continues until the next Avatara c=\r\nomes on earth. I am sure in the period after Rama, and before Krshna, of wh=\r\nich we have very little written record, the world at large remained entirel=\r\ny overawed by Rama Avatara.\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;In this light Krshna is the Poorna-Avatar=\r\na. When Kalki will appear on earth, he will be invarible accompanied by a s=\r\net of powerful Rishis - every Avatara comes with his coterie of Rishis who =\r\nexplain the philosophy and spirituality of the Avatara to the general masse=\r\ns - who will then create new scriptures and Kalki will be looked at as the =\r\ncrest jewel=A0of the Avataras.\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;*=A0 *=A0=A0 *\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;I believe in the =\r\nevolutionary parable of these 9 Avatara because I find no other reason why =\r\nthese set of Avatara, from the whole list of possible=A0Avataras, have capt=\r\nured the popular imagination. I mean Dattatreya is an Avatara too as per SB=\r\n. His spirituality is no less than that of any other Avatara. Yet, he is no=\r\nt in the list of 9/10 Avataras. \n&gt;=A0\n&gt;The=A0original Nath Yogis used to co=\r\nnsider=A0Nine Chakras in the Human Body. The idea of Kundalini Yoga also ca=\r\nme from them, which was basically exploring=A0cronologically all these nine=\r\n chakras one after the other by flooding them with Chit-Shakti.\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;There=\r\n are 9 basic grahas in jyotish. Each graha could very well=A0represent the =\r\nessential nature of each chakra. All these make me more sanguine that there=\r\n must be Nine Evolutionary Avataras, no