 became l=\r\ness natural and more effort was needed. So the &quot;spirit of patience, persist=\r\nence and\n hard-work&quot; (Saturn) became relevant and an avatara corresponding =\r\nto Saturn occurred. And so on.\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;In the dark ages of Kali yuga, rationa=\r\nl minds wouldn&#39;t accept anything that didn&#39;t &quot;make sense&quot;. Being establishe=\r\nd in Self became an unnatural, ridiculous and incomprehensible notion. So t=\r\nhe &quot;spirit of comprehension&quot; (Mercury) became relevant. An avatara correspo=\r\nnding to Mercury occurred and tried to explain being established in Self as=\r\n a comprehensible notion, so that rational minds of that age would accept i=\r\nt to an extent and attempt it.\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;Avataras occur based on the needs of c=\r\nollective consciousness. Of course, if one&#39;s consciousness is in a differen=\r\nt state from the collective consciousness of that time, the current avatara=\r\n may not be relevant to one.\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=\r\n=A0=A0 *\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt; I respect Rama, but I worship Krshna.\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;I am\n awestruc=\r\nk by Krishna and worship him, but I see Rama as an ideal that I MAY be able=\r\n to emulate oneday. In fact, I recommend the approach to others.\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;Thou=\r\ngh I said Rama and Krishna are almost the same, there is a difference betwe=\r\nen soul and perfected mind. Soul is a spark of Shiva and a perfected mind i=\r\ns a spark of Chit Shakti (whereas an imperfect mind is a spark of Maya shak=\r\nti).\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;\n&gt;Best regards, Narasimha -------- Astrology & Spirituality Reso=\r\nurces: http://www.vedicastrologer.org/\n&gt;--------\n&gt;=A0\n&gt;From: rajarshi nandy=\r\n &lt;rajarshi14@...&gt;\n&gt;&gt;To: &quot;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;vedic-wisdo=\r\nm@yahoogroups.com&gt; \n&gt;&gt;Sent: Sunday, May 5, 2013 3:34 AM\n&gt;&gt;Subject: Re: [ved=\r\nic-wisdom] Re: Comparing Dasavataras!\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;