a is the &quot;supreme&quot; one=\r\n and other deities are &quot;inferior&quot;; some would conclude that Surya is the &quot;s=\r\nupreme&quot; one and other deities are &quot;inferior&quot;; and so on.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=\r\n=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;On a different note, someone =\r\nmay think that Kali, being Aadyaa, is superior\n to Tara and like Kali more.=\r\n But, some learned yogis have declared them to be essentially the same and =\r\nsome scriptures even prohibited differentiating between them. As I see it, =\r\nthe difference between them is too subtle for even rishis to clearly compre=\r\nhend. People seeing some significant difference between them are, I am afra=\r\nid, merely projecting their own conditioning. Same in the case of Krishna a=\r\nnd Rama. Both were=A0 perfectly detached and fully divine karma yogis.\n&gt;&gt;=\r\n=A0\n&gt;&gt;If we think about it, perfected mind (paramatma aspect represented by=\r\n Moon) and soul (paramatma aspect represented by Sun) are not really that d=\r\nifferent. So I am afraid Krishna and Rama are not that different, though th=\r\ne specifics of their stories may be different.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;One last word though=\r\n. If someone truly believes that Krishna is superior to Rama and worships K=\r\nrishna (or vice versa!), I am very happy for such a person. My arguments ar=\r\ne more for the sake of sharing thinking/knowledge and pushing the boundarie=\r\ns of understanding in the long run, than changing the minds of anyone in th=\r\ne short run. In the end, everyone of us will have to go through one&#39;s own c=\r\nycles of various tamasik, rajasik and saattwik stages of evolution before o=\r\nne starts grasping some fistfuls of Reality. These concepts are too subtle =\r\nfor anyone to convince others or be absolutely confident oneself!\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;K=\r\nrishnarpanamastu, Narasimha -------- Astrology & Spirituality Resources: ht=\r\ntp://www.vedicastrol